message:
{{#is_alert}}
auth-service error rate is above 10% over the last 5 minutes.

## Runbook
1. Confirm degradation: `GET /actuator/health` on auth-service (look for db component DOWN / pool exhaustion).
2. Check the SRE Agent event stream (source:sre-incident-agent) for an automated RCA.
3. If the agent has NOT already remediated, disable the fault: `POST /api/v1/admin/chaos/deactivate`.
4. Recycle the DB connection pool and verify recovery via `/actuator/health`.
5. If error rate persists, page the platform on-call and follow https://runbooks.internal/auth-service/db-timeout

## Auto-remediation
The SRE Incident-Response Agent subscribes to this monitor's webhook and will attempt step 3 automatically; its RCA + outcome are published as a Datadog Event tagged `agent:sre-incident-agent`.
{{/is_alert}}
{{#is_recovery}}
auth-service error rate has recovered below threshold.
{{/is_recovery}}

@webhook-sre-agent @slack-platform-oncall
